The paper discusses the D4M toolbox, which is primarily used for data analytics and database connectivity. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.DB (Databases). The paper also discusses graph analytics and memory limitations, which could fall under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.LG (Machine Learning), respectively. The paper mentions the Julia programming language, which could fall under cs.PL (Programming Languages). Finally, the paper discusses complex analytics on unstructured data, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
